The National Emergency Management Agency, NEMA, has donated items to Zangan/Kirim communities in Takad Chiefdom, Kaura Local Government Area of Kaduna State. The community suffered series of attacks recently which left scores dead and properties destroyed. Presenting the items at the Central Primary School, Fadan Attakar, the Northwest Coordinator of NEMA, Ishaya Isa Chonoko, noted that the donation was meant to cushion the hardship experienced by the people. Chonoko urged the people to continue to embrace dialogue whenever there are disputes, and appealed to them to live in peace with their neighbours. In a remark, the member representing Kaura Constituency, who is also the Minority Whip in the House of Representatives, Gideon Gwani, commended the Takad people for picking up their lives after the attacks on their communities. Gwani also thanked NEMA for the gesture, adding that it would help in resettling some of those displaced after the attacks. Also in a remark, the Agwam Takad, Mr. Tobias Nkom Wada, thanked NEMA for the gesture and assured that the items would be equitably distributed. Items donated included bags of cement, assorted grains, bags of rice, bags of beans, roofing sheets, nylon mats, blankets and mattresses.  Kafanchan residents tasked on children education NEMA donates to attack  victims in Kaduna villages Breaking: Gunmen kill 14 persons in Kaura LG Kindly take one minute (1) of your time to fill out this short question. This questionnaire is designed to sample readers' opinions regarding what the feel about Daily Trust newspaper advertisement; it is not intended to used for any purpose other than to improve the quality of our newspapers. Any information provided will therefore be treated as confidential.